# Snapshots, encryption & instance store

## Snapshots

Point-in-time backup → **S3** (managed), **incremental**. Restore = new volume, any AZ (or another region after copy) — the way to move volumes across AZ/region.

- **Snapshot Archive** — ~75% cheaper, 24–72 h restore
- **Recycle Bin** — holds deleted snaps 1–365 days
- **Fast Snapshot Restore** — full performance immediately

## Encryption

AES-256 via **KMS**, transparent (Nitro, negligible overhead). Encrypted volume → encrypted snapshots. Flip **account default encryption** early (not retroactive).

## Instance Store

Local **NVMe**, millions IOPS — but **ephemeral** (gone on stop/terminate/host loss). For **caches, ML scratch, replicated systems** (Cassandra, Kafka).
